1
00:00:00,870 --> 00:00:03,170
Pops goes to visit a client because a warning note of a murder

2
00:00:03,170 --> 00:00:04,770
was delivered to him.

3
00:00:04,770 --> 00:00:06,570
But when he got there,

4
00:00:06,570 --> 00:00:08,670
his client, Mr. Yoichi Takarada,

5
00:00:08,670 --> 00:00:12,370
was stabbed to death by his secretary Mr. Haruyuki Shinkai.

6
00:00:13,570 --> 00:00:17,070
But the fact is Mr. Takarada had been strangled to death

7
00:00:17,070 --> 00:00:20,470
two hours before that!

8
00:00:20,470 --> 00:00:21,470
Mr. Shinkai is accused of

9
00:00:21,470 --> 00:00:24,170
"Haruyuki Shinkai (27)" -destruction of a corpse and was arrested.

10
00:00:24,170 --> 00:00:26,370
In the meantime, from the fingerprints on the warning note of a murder,

11
00:00:26,370 --> 00:00:28,070
"Koji Takarada (42)" -Mr. Takarada's younger brother, Mr. Koji,

12
00:00:28,070 --> 00:00:30,770
is suspected of committing the crime

13
00:00:30,770 --> 00:00:32,570
but thanks to the testimony of Mr. Shinkai,

14
00:00:32,570 --> 00:00:34,970
Mr. Koji is spared of suspicion.

15
00:00:34,970 --> 00:00:37,170
On the other hand, his wife Mika, is suspected.

16
00:00:37,170 --> 00:00:38,170
"Mika Takarada (36)" -Furthermore,

17
00:00:38,170 --> 00:00:40,470
with the discovery of a wig that served as concrete evidence,

18
00:00:40,470 --> 00:00:43,370
suspicion about her seems even more conclusive.

19
00:00:45,670 --> 00:00:47,470
A canvas stained black with crime.

20
00:00:47,470 --> 00:00:49,870
Vivid brilliant deduction skills change its color.

21
00:00:49,870 --> 00:00:51,970
Take a good look at the three suspects.

22
00:00:51,970 --> 00:00:54,070
One of them is a big liar!

23
00:00:54,070 --> 00:00:55,670
He sees through the one and only truth.

24
00:00:55,670 --> 00:00:57,670
A child in appearance with the I.Q. of an adult.

25
00:00:57,670 --> 00:01:00,170
His name is Detective Conan!

26
00:02:46,828 --> 00:02:51,828
"The Man Who Died Twice (Part 2)"

27
00:02:51,828 --> 00:02:54,828
"Mouri Detective Agency" -She still hasnt confessed?

28
00:02:54,828 --> 00:02:58,328
She looked pretty sly.

29
00:02:58,328 --> 00:03:00,528
You must have it tough, Inspector.

30
00:03:00,528 --> 00:03:02,228
If Mrs. Takarada is framed

31
00:03:02,228 --> 00:03:05,228
and made to look as if she had murdered her husband,

32
00:03:05,228 --> 00:03:08,328
she would lose her right to inheritance

33
00:03:08,328 --> 00:03:12,528
and his younger brother, Koji, would inherit everything.

34
00:03:12,528 --> 00:03:15,328
He probably planned on doing so

35
00:03:15,328 --> 00:03:19,328
but the problem is Mr. Shinkai's testimony of his alibi.

36
00:03:19,328 --> 00:03:21,928
Was his testimony false?

37
00:03:21,928 --> 00:03:23,728
What're you mumbling about?

38
00:03:23,728 --> 00:03:27,528
What? No. Its nothing.

39
00:03:27,528 --> 00:03:29,528
Yes.

40
00:03:29,528 --> 00:03:33,328
About Mr. Haruyuki Shinkai who was arrested yesterday.

41
00:03:33,328 --> 00:03:34,928
I have something I want to discuss.

42
00:03:34,928 --> 00:03:37,528
Well, please have a seat.

43
00:03:39,328 --> 00:03:42,228
I am Hisashi Teshima.

44
00:03:42,228 --> 00:03:43,528
I see.

45
00:03:43,528 --> 00:03:46,828
You work at a printing factory?

46
00:03:46,828 --> 00:03:49,928
And? What did you want to say about Mr. Shinkai?

47
00:03:49,928 --> 00:03:51,728
"Hisashi Teshima (28)" -Both Shinkai and I

48
00:03:51,728 --> 00:03:56,028
were raised in the same orphanage.

49
00:03:56,028 --> 00:04:00,528
That's why I came wanting to help make his crime a little lighter.

50
00:04:02,028 --> 00:04:06,028
Since you seems to have witnessed him committing the crime.

51
00:04:06,028 --> 00:04:08,328
Thats why you came to me?

52
00:04:08,328 --> 00:04:09,428
Yes.

53
00:04:09,428 --> 00:04:12,728
Shinkai is not a bad guy.

54
00:04:12,728 --> 00:04:16,128
He was abandoned by a super selfish mother.

55
00:04:16,128 --> 00:04:17,928
I feel sorry for him.

56
00:04:17,928 --> 00:04:19,628
Super selfish mother?

57
00:04:19,628 --> 00:04:22,028
Kid, stay out of this!

58
00:04:23,328 --> 00:04:26,428
Mr. Teshima, I understand how you feel,

59
00:04:26,428 --> 00:04:29,828
but I think you should discuss things like this with a lawyer.

60
00:04:29,828 --> 00:04:33,428
Its not within my sphere of work.

61
00:04:33,428 --> 00:04:35,228
A lawyer.

62
00:04:35,228 --> 00:04:39,128
Yes. I'm sure a lawyer can be of help to you.

63
00:04:40,328 --> 00:04:42,128
All right.

64
00:04:42,128 --> 00:04:44,728
I'm sorry to have intruded on you despite your busy schedule.

65
00:04:44,728 --> 00:04:47,328
No problem, I'm sorry I couldn't be of help to you.

66
00:04:47,328 --> 00:04:48,428
Goodbye.

67
00:04:51,028 --> 00:04:53,628
Pops, I'm going out for a while too.

68
00:04:53,628 --> 00:04:55,628
Hey, brat.

69
00:04:55,628 --> 00:04:58,328
What's with him?

70
00:04:59,928 --> 00:05:02,528
Oh, boy. He doesnt know how to clean up.

71
00:05:05,228 --> 00:05:08,628
What is it you want to confirm with me?

72
00:05:08,628 --> 00:05:11,928
When Mr. Takarada was killed around 1 pm yesterday,

73
00:05:11,928 --> 00:05:15,128
you were at a department store in Shinjuku, right?

74
00:05:16,428 --> 00:05:19,728
Yeah. So what do you want confirm?

75
00:05:19,728 --> 00:05:22,728
It seems that Mr. Shinkai, who testified to your alibi,

76
00:05:22,728 --> 00:05:26,128
is saying that he lied about it

77
00:05:26,128 --> 00:05:30,028
because he was being threatened by you.

78
00:05:30,028 --> 00:05:31,528
That guy!

79
00:05:31,528 --> 00:05:33,728
Why would he lie like that!

80
00:05:33,728 --> 00:05:35,728
Is he lying?

81
00:05:35,728 --> 00:05:39,528
Tell Detective Mouri who sent you here.

82
00:05:39,528 --> 00:05:42,728
That it's no use suspecting me.

83
00:05:42,728 --> 00:05:44,128
I've got other people to testify for me

84
00:05:44,128 --> 00:05:46,928
besides that secretary too, you know?

85
00:05:46,928 --> 00:05:48,328
What?

86
00:05:48,328 --> 00:05:51,328
I was called out by phone yesterday

87
00:05:51,328 --> 00:05:53,628
from a guy I dont know.

88
00:05:53,628 --> 00:05:56,328
He told me that he knew of a good job to make money of.

89
00:05:56,328 --> 00:05:59,228
I was stood up though.

90
00:05:59,228 --> 00:06:01,528
But when I was waiting for that man...

91
00:06:01,528 --> 00:06:04,028
Hey you! I found you, Koji!

92
00:06:04,028 --> 00:06:05,228
Bummers!

93
00:06:05,228 --> 00:06:06,328
Hold it!

94
00:06:06,328 --> 00:06:09,428
Give me back my money, Koji!

95
00:06:09,428 --> 00:06:13,428
He's a guy named Yaginuma who I cheated money out of before.

96
00:06:13,428 --> 00:06:17,528
I was composed even when the police suspected me

97
00:06:17,528 --> 00:06:21,928
because I figured Yaginuma could testify for me in the end.

98
00:06:21,928 --> 00:06:25,128
Although he may beat me to a pulp.

99
00:06:28,328 --> 00:06:32,928
It seems he's not lying.

100
00:06:32,928 --> 00:06:36,528
Isn't that what you call fishing in troubled water?

101
00:06:36,528 --> 00:06:38,428
What does he mean by you ran an errand for me?

102
00:06:38,428 --> 00:06:43,228
Listen. The one who murdered Takarada is his wife!

103
00:06:43,228 --> 00:06:46,728
She called a man to summon Koji out

104
00:06:46,728 --> 00:06:50,428
and erased his alibi to frame him as the perpetrator!

105
00:06:51,528 --> 00:06:53,128
But Pops!

106
00:06:53,128 --> 00:06:56,328
If so, dont you think its too sloppy?

107
00:06:57,528 --> 00:06:58,528
What do you mean?

108
00:06:58,528 --> 00:07:00,328
If she wanted to erase his alibi,

109
00:07:00,328 --> 00:07:01,428
she'd want to call him out to a secluded place

110
00:07:01,428 --> 00:07:03,628
with no other people around, right?

111
00:07:03,628 --> 00:07:04,728
Because she didn't do so,

112
00:07:04,728 --> 00:07:08,428
a witness like Mr. Yaginuma appeared.

113
00:07:08,428 --> 00:07:10,928
Even the wig that serves as evidence is found

114
00:07:10,928 --> 00:07:14,328
because it was thrown away very sloppily.

115
00:07:14,328 --> 00:07:16,628
Geez, what a nuisance.

116
00:07:16,628 --> 00:07:21,028
In other words, shes dumb, that selfish woman.

117
00:07:21,028 --> 00:07:22,428
What?

118
00:07:26,928 --> 00:07:30,728
Is it okay to finish it off with just one word, like dumb?

119
00:07:34,328 --> 00:07:38,328
I think its unlikely that Mrs. Mika is the perpetrator.

120
00:07:38,328 --> 00:07:39,528
Which means...

121
00:07:40,728 --> 00:07:42,028
I see!

122
00:07:42,028 --> 00:07:45,628
That's why it had to be found!

123
00:07:45,628 --> 00:07:48,028
If so...

124
00:07:48,028 --> 00:07:51,828
They found fingerprints on the murder warning note.

125
00:07:51,828 --> 00:07:55,528
Mr. Koji Takarada, your fingerprints!

126
00:07:55,528 --> 00:07:59,128
It was supposed to be Mika's fingerprints.

127
00:08:00,528 --> 00:08:01,828
Wait a second.

128
00:08:01,828 --> 00:08:03,228
It's only natural, right?

129
00:08:03,228 --> 00:08:08,028
Because we've found that he's the perpetrator and the case is closed.

130
00:08:08,028 --> 00:08:09,728
Which means...

131
00:08:09,728 --> 00:08:14,028
But, if so why did he do something like that?

132
00:08:14,028 --> 00:08:16,028
He contrived it just for that?

133
00:08:16,028 --> 00:08:19,728
Which means, it had all started from the beginning.

134
00:08:27,628 --> 00:08:30,328
That brat. He's up to something again.

135
00:08:30,328 --> 00:08:31,528
"Mouri Detective Agency"

136
00:08:31,528 --> 00:08:33,828
Okay. I understand.

137
00:08:33,828 --> 00:08:36,628
No, something kept bothering me.

138
00:08:36,628 --> 00:08:38,728
Goodbye.

139
00:08:38,728 --> 00:08:40,328
I thought so.

140
00:08:40,328 --> 00:08:41,728
Thats why.

141
00:08:41,728 --> 00:08:42,928
Hey, glasses kid!

142
00:08:42,928 --> 00:08:45,328
What stupid idea did you come up with?

143
00:08:45,328 --> 00:08:47,128
Next time you use my name,

144
00:08:47,128 --> 00:08:48,428
I'll teach you a lesson, understand?

145
00:08:49,528 --> 00:08:52,928
No matter what kind of background he may have come from...

146
00:08:54,528 --> 00:08:56,628
He's quite famous

147
00:08:56,628 --> 00:09:00,528
for loving to wear flashy things.

148
00:09:00,528 --> 00:09:03,628
What if there's a blonde wig or something?

149
00:09:03,628 --> 00:09:06,228
He's sure to wear it!

150
00:09:06,228 --> 00:09:08,728
He'd be delighted.

151
00:09:08,728 --> 00:09:10,928
That's why he took it there.

152
00:09:16,628 --> 00:09:19,828
Just as expected of a great detective like Mr. Mouri.

153
00:09:19,828 --> 00:09:24,128
Like what Mr. Mouri said, I got a call from one of the residents.

154
00:09:24,128 --> 00:09:26,428
"Kinsaku Tomii (58)" -It was an anonymous caller.

155
00:09:26,428 --> 00:09:29,828
But he said that a suspicious person seems to have gone upstairs.

156
00:09:29,828 --> 00:09:33,028
That's why I went to make my rounds

157
00:09:33,028 --> 00:09:36,028
and encountered that blonde woman.

158
00:09:36,028 --> 00:09:38,728
Just as I thought, it wasn't a coincidence.

159
00:09:46,228 --> 00:09:49,128
The only thing needed now is decisive evidence.

160
00:09:55,228 --> 00:09:56,828
Come to think of it, back then...

161
00:10:06,528 --> 00:10:09,228
Just what's going on, Inspector?

162
00:10:09,228 --> 00:10:11,628
What do you mean?

163
00:10:11,628 --> 00:10:14,528
You're the one that told me to bring these three here, right?

164
00:10:14,528 --> 00:10:15,628
What?

165
00:10:15,628 --> 00:10:19,028
You're the one who said youve figured out the truth of the case.

166
00:10:26,028 --> 00:10:27,528
So, now, people.

167
00:10:27,528 --> 00:10:30,828
It's time for me to tell you all about this case.

168
00:10:43,895 --> 00:10:48,195
We made a mistake from the very start.

169
00:10:48,195 --> 00:10:50,795
We assumed that someone in the family was responsible for the murder,

170
00:10:50,795 --> 00:10:54,195
and by doing so we immediately eliminated the real perpetrator.

171
00:10:55,295 --> 00:10:57,595
Eliminated the real perpetrator?

172
00:10:57,595 --> 00:10:58,795
Yes.

173
00:10:58,795 --> 00:11:02,495
The perpetrator who killed Mr. Yoichi Takarada is...

174
00:11:02,495 --> 00:11:05,695
Mr. Haruyuki Shinkai over there!

175
00:11:11,195 --> 00:11:14,195
Mr. Shinkai is the perpetrator?

176
00:11:14,195 --> 00:11:15,595
Mr. Mouri?

177
00:11:15,595 --> 00:11:19,595
If he strangled Mr. Takarada to death,

178
00:11:19,595 --> 00:11:25,195
then why did he have to stab Mr. Takarada again two hours later?

179
00:11:25,195 --> 00:11:27,795
Rather to begin with

180
00:11:27,795 --> 00:11:30,295
I have an alibi at the time

181
00:11:30,295 --> 00:11:32,695
when the president was killed.

182
00:11:32,695 --> 00:11:34,495
It's true that Mr. Shinkai confessed that

183
00:11:34,495 --> 00:11:37,795
as long as Mr. Takarada was around,

184
00:11:37,795 --> 00:11:40,795
new victims will keep being created so he had plans to kill him.

185
00:11:40,795 --> 00:11:45,695
But that's not why he murdered Mr. Takarada.

186
00:11:45,695 --> 00:11:49,195
Mr. Shinkai, as Mr. Takarada's secretary,

187
00:11:49,195 --> 00:11:54,895
you knew that Mika remained married to Mr. Takarada for his money.

188
00:11:54,895 --> 00:11:58,195
Where is all this coming from all of a sudden?

189
00:11:58,195 --> 00:12:00,995
Mr. Takarada probably told you himself

190
00:12:00,995 --> 00:12:03,695
that he had only six months to live.

191
00:12:03,695 --> 00:12:06,395
In other words, in six months,

192
00:12:06,395 --> 00:12:08,295
she'd be inheriting the entire estate

193
00:12:08,295 --> 00:12:11,295
and insurance money that shed long waited for.

194
00:12:11,295 --> 00:12:13,795
And you couldn't stand that.

195
00:12:16,995 --> 00:12:18,895
That's when you came up with the idea

196
00:12:18,895 --> 00:12:20,895
of killing Mr. Takarada

197
00:12:20,895 --> 00:12:24,695
and framing Mika as the killer.

198
00:12:24,695 --> 00:12:28,995
Then she would lose the right to inherit his estate

199
00:12:28,995 --> 00:12:30,395
and his insurance money.

200
00:12:31,895 --> 00:12:36,295
In other words, it's not that you really wanted to kill Mr. Takarada,

201
00:12:36,295 --> 00:12:39,595
but you killed him only to frame Mika up

202
00:12:39,595 --> 00:12:41,695
for killing her husband.

203
00:12:41,695 --> 00:12:44,495
What?

204
00:12:44,495 --> 00:12:48,295
You're not making any sense.

205
00:12:48,295 --> 00:12:52,395
It seems you have your mind set on making me the real perpetrator,

206
00:12:52,395 --> 00:12:55,095
but you just contradicted yourself.

207
00:12:55,095 --> 00:12:57,495
If I wanted to frame her as the murderer,

208
00:12:57,495 --> 00:13:02,295
I would've had to put her fingerprints on the murder warning note!

209
00:13:02,295 --> 00:13:05,395
But my fingerprints were on it.

210
00:13:05,395 --> 00:13:07,195
True.

211
00:13:07,195 --> 00:13:09,395
It's contradictory.

212
00:13:09,395 --> 00:13:14,295
When Koji, the perfect pawn, came to the house,

213
00:13:14,295 --> 00:13:16,895
you put your plan into action.

214
00:13:16,895 --> 00:13:20,295
Why aren't you answering my counterargument?

215
00:13:20,295 --> 00:13:22,595
You created a murder warning note

216
00:13:22,595 --> 00:13:25,495
with Kojis fingerprints on it then sent it.

217
00:13:25,495 --> 00:13:28,295
So, I'm telling you that's contradictory!

218
00:13:28,295 --> 00:13:30,495
That arrived yesterday.

219
00:13:30,495 --> 00:13:33,095
I'd like to see them try it!

220
00:13:36,795 --> 00:13:42,595
Later, you urged Mr. Takarada to confine himself to this study alone.

221
00:13:42,595 --> 00:13:43,695
While on the other hand,

222
00:13:43,695 --> 00:13:47,795
you told Mika that the president wanted her

223
00:13:47,795 --> 00:13:50,695
to organize the storeroom to make sure she stayed at home.

224
00:13:50,695 --> 00:13:53,095
Ma'am, you were asked by your husband

225
00:13:53,095 --> 00:13:55,895
to organize the storeroom, correct?

226
00:13:55,895 --> 00:13:59,495
Yes, but I wasn't told to do so directly.

227
00:13:59,495 --> 00:14:02,795
I relayed the message from the president to her.

228
00:14:02,795 --> 00:14:05,095
You planned this so she would have no one

229
00:14:05,095 --> 00:14:06,995
to back up her alibi.

230
00:14:06,995 --> 00:14:10,395
But the house maid was at the house too.

231
00:14:10,395 --> 00:14:13,595
You knew that she'd be going out, didnt you?

232
00:14:13,595 --> 00:14:14,595
"Kyoko, Afternoon, Hospital" -Yes.

233
00:14:14,595 --> 00:14:18,095
Not only Koji, but I'm sure that everyone else knew too.

234
00:14:18,095 --> 00:14:20,195
Because as soon as I got the appointment,

235
00:14:20,195 --> 00:14:21,195
I marked it on the calendar like this

236
00:14:21,195 --> 00:14:23,595
because I didn't want to inconvenience anybody.

237
00:14:23,595 --> 00:14:26,995
I may have heard about it, but I forgot.

238
00:14:26,995 --> 00:14:29,195
Then, you called me,

239
00:14:29,195 --> 00:14:31,395
pretending to be Mr. Takarada.

240
00:14:31,395 --> 00:14:33,295
Since I never met him,

241
00:14:33,295 --> 00:14:36,295
I had no idea what he would sound like.

242
00:14:36,295 --> 00:14:39,395
You have no proof either that I made the call.

243
00:14:39,395 --> 00:14:41,695
You also pretended to be an imaginary person

244
00:14:41,695 --> 00:14:45,095
and got Koji to leave the house.

245
00:14:45,095 --> 00:14:47,195
Was that you?

246
00:14:47,195 --> 00:14:50,295
You dont have proof that it was me then, either.

247
00:14:50,295 --> 00:14:54,795
Then, at 1 pm you came to this condominium.

248
00:14:54,795 --> 00:14:58,595
I followed Koji and was in Shinjuku

249
00:14:58,595 --> 00:15:00,395
among the crowd of parents and children there who came to watch.

250
00:15:00,395 --> 00:15:02,295
The hero show.

251
00:15:02,295 --> 00:15:04,095
If you insist you followed him there,

252
00:15:04,095 --> 00:15:08,195
then perhaps you can tell us about the commotion that occurred.

253
00:15:08,195 --> 00:15:10,495
Theres no way you didnt see it

254
00:15:10,495 --> 00:15:12,995
if you were really there.

255
00:15:12,995 --> 00:15:15,395
Hey, you! I found you, Koji!

256
00:15:15,395 --> 00:15:16,795
Bummers!

257
00:15:16,795 --> 00:15:18,695
Hold it!

258
00:15:18,695 --> 00:15:22,295
You could've known about the hero show ahead of time,

259
00:15:22,295 --> 00:15:23,595
and you could've assumed that

260
00:15:23,595 --> 00:15:26,195
